    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date>20 April 1830 1850 (?)</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">So favorable an opportunity as this cannot escape me to say<lb/> a
                few words to you after the lapse of time intervened. The state of our<lb/> uncle's
                health is exceedingly delicate, his limbs will scarcely bear him<lb/> along. So
                debilitated is he by the wretched cough attendant on his asthma.<lb/> Rest has he
                none by day or night, and altho he has had strength enough<lb/> to crawl to my
                office I really think he will not get home without extreme<lb/> fatigue. I do not
                mention these facts with a view of inducing you to<lb/> come or should it interfere
                in your arrangements. But I am certain a<lb/> few days of your company with uncle
                would so gratify him that the experi-<lb/>ment is worth trying. Could you not be
                spared a few days next week? I<lb/> am not so sure that I am not taking upon myself
                a responsibility in<lb/> these remarks that might induce you to come on at all
                hazards. Our<lb/> friend <persName>Mr. Etting</persName> will tell you how
                debilitated and feeble uncle looks,<lb/> and I am only giving you my own impression
                what I think would delight him.<lb/> Contrary to        the least idea that I have
                made this communi-<lb/>cation. Hence <hi rend="underline">should</hi> you come, say
                that you heard that uncle was sick<lb/> and having a few days leisure you came over
                to see him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Mama has been confined to her bed &amp; room for some weeks tho<lb/>
                so far recovered as to speak of coming down <add>Hebrew</add> God willing.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">A letter from <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> yesterday. All well
                &amp; things is<lb/> status quo.<lb/> Happiness attend you.<lb/> Yours,</p>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">D. Judah</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Addressed<lb/>
                <sic><addressee>Rev Isaac Leezer</addressee></sic><lb/> attention<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs Etting</persName></p>
        </body>
